      <div class="box1">
        <h1>Jumping Jumbalaya</h1>
        <h2>Jumbalaya</h2>
        <p>Recipe By: Southern Living</p>
        <figure>
          <img src="Jumbalaya.jpg" alt="Top Tier Jumbalaya" style="width:100%;">
          <figcaption>A beautifully cooked bowl of Jumbalaya</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <div class="box2">
        <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1 pound andouille sausage, sliced</li>
          <li>2 tablespoons canola oil</li>
          <li>2 cups diced sweet onion</li>
          <li>1 cup diced celery</li>
          <li>1 large red bell pepper, diced</li>
          <li>4 garlic cloves, minced</li>
          <li>1 bay leaf</li>
          <li>1 teaspoon dried oregano</li>
          <li>2 teaspoons Creole seasoning</li>
          <li>1 teaspoon dried thyme</li>
          <li>2 (10 oz) cans diced tomatoes and green chiles, drained</li>
          <li>3 cups chicken broth</li>
          <li>2 cups uncooked long-grain rice</li>
          <li>2 cups shredded cooked chicken</li>
          <li>1 pound peeled, raw shrimp, deveined</li>
          <li>1/2 cup chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley</li>
          <li>Garnish: chopped green onions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="box3">
        <h3 class="rate">Rate This Recipe</h3>
        <fieldset>
          <legend>How difficult is this recipe?</legend>
          <input type="radio" id="easy" name="difficulty"> Easy
          <input type="radio" id="med" name="difficulty"> Intermediate
          <input type="radio" id="hard" name="difficulty"> Hard
        </fieldset>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <div class="conversion">
          <h3>Conversion</h3>
          <input type="text" id="tblspn" name="tblspn">
          =
          <input type="text" id="cups" name="cups">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="directions">
        <h3>Directions</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Cook sausage in hot oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until browned.</li>
          <li>Remove sausage with slotted spoon.</li>
          <li>Add diced onions and next 7 ingredients to hot drippings; saut√© 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.</li>
          <li>Stir in tomatoes, next 3 ingredients, and sausage.</li>
          <li>Bring to boil over high heat.</li>
          <li>Cover, reduce heat to medium, and simmer, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until rice is tender.</li>
          <li>Stir in shrimp; cover and cook 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.</li>
          <li>Stir in parsley.</li>
          <li>Serve immediately.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

